< Text>
I have been on the Dr Steffes hype for some time since my family has used him for many small exotics so when my cat was very sick, he was the man I thought of first!

My cat had issues her entire life with chronic respiratory infections and low platelets and other things.  My usual vet sort of said ‚Äúeh shes old and will die soon‚Äù but I wasn‚Äôt going to agree with that... I mean, my grandma is old too, should I stop taking her to the doctors?

Anyway, I emailed back and forth initially, almost with instant responses, and was scheduled to come in.  When I got there, only one other person was there at the time.  When I met with Dr Steffes, he noticed that my cat was walking around exploring the room and instead of stressing her more by forcing her to be up on the table, he laid on the floor with her and spent time listening to her breathe, and watching the way her chest moved.  When he told me what he thought with her history and medications she had been on, he gave me a couple of hypotheticals. I asked, ‚Äúwhat would you do if this was your cat?‚Äù And he gave me an answer.  It was so heart warming and positive in spirit and he gave her lots of love, too.

I don‚Äôt know if he knew I was struggling or his prices were just so acceptable, but the visit and medication seemed appropriately priced, and not like he was trying to pay off med school with my income alone... I was so delighted even though I was crying like a baby.

Blackie went on to live about 2 more years.. she was my best friend, and I miss her tons.  We need more doctors like Dr Steffes!<//Text>

< review>
Livermore, CA

5.0 star rating 3/13/2017
Wow - what a great practice!  I've got pit bulls & my big boy can be kind of a jerk toward strangers, & especially toward men.  While mentioning my concerns to my contractor (also a pittie-lover) he referred me to his sister's practice at Ohana Animal Hospital.  I'm so pleased!

The reception & waiting room is beautifully calm & the techs so considerate to my touchy anxious boy - providing grain-free treats for his cranky tummy.  Dr, Hacker won over my dog in a matter of moments & while a little tense, he was a very good boy during his exam & blood draws.

The love, care, & sensitivity shown toward my dog & his great response to the staff have sealed the deal - Nikabrik has found his new doctor!  Bonus: Dr. Steffes treats rabbits!  Now my buns will have an doctor close to home who understands their temperments & special needs.

If you're looking for a new veterinary practice, I highly recommend Ohana!< /review>

< review>
Quick summery: You will not be able to find a more caring vet than Dr. Steffes. Feel free bring your animal here with zero worries about the quality of care and attention you will receive.

Long Story: We met Dr. Steffes back in March of 2016. We had a bearded dragon Falcor that was going through some medical distress and was referred over to Zach. After bringing in Falcor for an examination it was obvious that she was suffering from very unique and strange medical problems. He had to drain fluid from around her heart, and it was sent off to be tested. Over the next few weeks Dr. Steffs ran multiple tests, provided us with a feeding and medication plan, kept in contact via email and phone, and made himself available appointments at the hospital when needed. Zach also took the time to explain all of the medical issues, possible complications and answer any questions we had about them or treatment options.

At no point did Dr Steffes give us anything but courteous and caring service, even though I am sure we imposed more than we should have on his time. Our bearded dragon was suffering from more than one aliment and ultimately died, but when she passed we knew that there was absolutely nothing else that could have been done for her, and because of the care she received we were able to enjoy her company far longer than without.

But it was not just Falcor that received excellent treatment. Our Chinchillas, cats and dogs all came to Dr. Steffes if there was a need and every one of them was treated with love and care while with him. I would feel comfortable giving any animal to his care and recommend him without any reservations to anyone that is looking for quality vet care.< /review>

< Review>
Sorry to see Our long time family fave for years has closed down. We'll miss the BEST mongolian bbq‚òπ. 5 stars is not only for the great $ & service but also for the taste and quality of food and value for your dollar. They offered 4 meat choices plus shrimp, lots of vegetable choices, 3 sauces-lobster, kung pao and soy, sesame oil, white wine, minced garlic, ginger, chili paste. Your meal included: rice, soup and hot bread pockets. Other mongolian places we tried years before can't hold a torch to this place.
I'm hoping the new place opening up at this address will be the same taste, quality and value for the price.< /Review>

< date>
1340927306566</date>
<Rate>4<//Rate><review>So, I love this place. They aren't so fussy about the decor, or even the maintenance of their seating. But here's the kicker, it's self serve buffet style mongolian barbecue!

You could probably go to a more expensive place to see a cleaner decor, but if you're looking for a "hole in the wall" type of place in North Orange County, this is your place.

Also, this is the only Mongolian bbq where I've had lamb as one of the meats!

#tip

When you enter, they will point you to where you sit. After you sit, they'll take your order, basically, either you do: all you can eat or a single serving. The meals come with a drink, rice, bread pouch and soup (the soup is just a house soup and a hit or miss on thickness). It's a really good deal.<//review><pictures>None< /pictures><resp>None</resp>< GmapID>

I have mild Scoleosis or curvature of the spine, quite common, having gotten a walk-in, first-time patient special for an adjustment, I signed up for some sessions in bulk because of the dollar benefit saved here.  I've been going to The Joint at least every other day usually for $10 per sessioin due to my subscription plan, and not only is my chronic back pain which was at 99% pain, generally at 30% max now, I'm not a doctor but I'm trying to articulate the phenomenon here, it is as if my spine was pressing against my lung at an angle that limited my breathing and they fixed it: massive relief and better well being.  I've been to Dr. Bystrom, Dr. Wynn and Dr. Escobar at the Joint Chriporactic in Van Nuys, and each has a mildly different approach to adjusting and all three are very effective approaches. Most of all The Joint is very affordable and it's now become a chain so I get work done on my back when I'm in the city too. P.S. I love the new Weho location! However I wish my Sherman Oaks location was open earlier! I have to wait 2-4 hours for you guys to open bc my back always gets me up early from pain. I get all of my errands done and find myself back at home in pain, sitting in the couch bc I'm waiting for you to guys to open. My regular doctor opens at 8am I wish you guys opened at 9am at least. I still love my Sherman Oaks location the most though.< /Review>

< text>
Ordered the bratwurst burrito, T-Mex Sausage with Southwestern tots and a cold 805. The food was delicious and I definitely ordered more than I could eat. The sausage was juicy, had great flavor, fresh toppings, soft bread and good sauce. Tater tots were so crunchy outside, tasty sauce and cheese. Burrito was hefty and filling with good flavor. Washed it all down with a cold 805. The staff was friendly and it was clean inside. Thankfully they had outside seating, cute lights across the top and a tv playing football. It's located along a strip of other shops and there's a pretty big parking lot in the back. They have a bunch other tasty options so will definitely be back.<//text>

<Text>DogHaus was awesome. They have so many options of hot dogs, links and burgers. The quality was excellent and the presentation of the food very nice. <name>Rick Lupert</name>< date>
1518981885019<//date>
<Rating>4</Rating>< review>
As a vegetarian who didn‚Äôt give up meat because I didn‚Äôt like it, I‚Äôm always thrilled to be treated like a ‚Äúfull citizen‚Äù at meat-centric restaurants, and I got that treatment here at The Dog Haus (Northridge, CA location) where they have a veggie hot dog, a veggie sausage, and a veggie burger all available to go on any of their menu items.

It‚Äôs an order at the counter, small-ish establishment with craft beers on top and a family friendly / bar environment.

I was glad I could order anything off the menu and specify the vegetarian protein I wanted in it, though I rolled-my own with the the vegan apple sage sausage with mustard, onions and sauerkraut and cheddar cheese. This was super yummy. The flavor and texture of the veggie sausage was spot-on‚Ä¶the bun was perfect and I would definitely eat this again!

I also had tots on the side‚Ä¶these were perfectly cooked, not over done, not underdone‚Ä¶just the right amount of crispy on the outside with the inside being as tender as it should be.

Pair that with the stout on draft beer and I felt like a full fledged human being eating at a meat restaurant despite my vegetarianism. It was all super-yummy!

My son had a veggie hot dog with ketchup. He didn‚Äôt love it but I think it‚Äôs because there was too much ketchup on it, but in my eyes the veggie dog itself on his sandwich looked pretty good, and large (unlike the small veggie dogs you see in packages in the market.)

Since I was dining in, I wish the beer had come in a real glass, even a reusable plastic stein instead of a throw away plastic cup. I saw someone drinking from a large stein and think if people are dining in they should automatically serve in reusable glasses instead of throw-awayables (or at least ask what you want there...better for the environment and "nices up" the experience a bit to not be drinking out of a plastic cup,  but other than that I loved the meal there. The service was super-friendly and fast and I will definitely be back again!<//review>

< Text>
DogHaus was awesome. They have so many options of hot dogs, links and burgers. The quality was excellent and the presentation of the food very nice. The groupon is def worth it, but without a groupon, the prices are still affordable. For vegetarians, they have a veggie dog and sides you could munch on. The portions are good, so you may not need to get a side with your hotdog or burger. Other than that, it was worth the visit, I drove from LA to Northridge. The restaurant felt like a fancy "millenial" wienerschiztel...idk if I spelled that right, but hope you got my drift. You can dine-in or take out. This is one of my fave new spots.< /Text>

Darlene Thompson< /username>
< time>
1582788671240< /time>
<Rate>5< /Rate>< Review>
WARNING LONG READ! I had a bad experience about a month or so ago. Last night I went back by myself, to the same DogHaus, ordered my food and waited for takeout. I purchased a Groupon voucher the day of my bad experience, and didn't use it. My niece, who's recently paralyzed in L.A. told me she wanted to see me, and to bring something new and different from the valley. I thought to myself she might like the Dog Haus. I ordered the Mensch, spicy chicken, and  cheesy taters. Due,to me using a voucher you must dine in. The young man explain to me the dilemma, but he honored me a one-time courtesy. I didn't have to explain anything to him,  he was extremely generous and courteous. It was late and I was not looking forward to the ride to L.A..  While waiting, I had a chance to watch the young lady at the register, she was very welcoming to all who approached her, and very patient. She also acknowledged other customers as they were walking in to dine. While I was there  the line became very long, but everyone was pleasant. This gave me a sense that they too know that love, and comfort food is being served in this establishment. When my food was delivered to me the gentlemen informed me, that he had given me a 10% discount on my next order. I thought that was nice. I'm  so glad that I'm  a person of second chances. I experienced an easy flow ordering, food cooked to order, and a goody with delivered. All this to say that the drive to LA was not what I  wanted, but my niece eating those cheesy taters w/ ketchup was priceless. She loved them more than she loved the Spicy Chicken. She ate the sandwich and we got to stay up til 4am, talking about the last 2 months of 2020. Thanks Dog Haus, I don't drink beer, but I will be bringing my folks whenever they come to the valley to  visit.< /Review>

<rating>4</rating><text>Excellent burgers and sides.  This is NOT your typical fast food.  It's a premium  burger or dog.  Those complaining about "overpriced" need to understand this.

The burgers are generous.  You taste REAL beef, not "breaded" by product.  I've had both the onion rings and tots.  The rings are excellent and the tots are not greasy.  The service has been friendly each time I've gone.  I look forward to returning.  I appreciate the classic rock music and overall atmosphere.  The servers are attentive and the food orders are quick, especially when burgers are made to order.

If you love burgers, Dog  Haus is a must.< /text>< pics>

ZAHRA HUSEIN<//name>
<time>1550680497058< /time><rate>3< /rate><Text>I used to really like this place, but the time before last I tried to order my usual and they had changed their plant-based sausage. I hadn't tried the Beyond Sausage before, but I figured I'd give it a go. After ordering and waiting nearly 30 minutes for 2 hot dogs to go, I noticed on my receipt it just said 'bratwurst' so I asked the cashier who rung me up if that was for the Beyond Bratwurst I ordered and he said "yeah, bratwurst" and I asked again "BEYOND bratwurst?" And he looked so confused and just shrugged and said "bratwurst" again. At this point the owner of this location comes over. Let me also add that on their menu, it is literally labelled as "Beyond Bratwurst" if you don't even know the name of something on the menu right behind you, I have no idea how to help you understand. The owner at this point understands what I am saying and begins to make excuses for her employee saying that the menu is new and they haven't gotten used to it. Then she tells me that it'll take another 30 minutes because the vegan meats are kept frozen, but if I want I can just have the regular bratwurst because it's almost done. She says this implying that it is my fault it'll take longer by being vegan when in reality if her employee had just listened to me it would've been finished at that point. I was clearly upset still so she offered to give me a refund. I paid with the mobile app because I forgot my wallet at home and she said there was nothing she could do to refund me since I used the app. I understand that's not her fault, but if she's the owner she should've been able to figure out another way to refund me. She eventually gave me two coupons for free items which didn't really help me because it was only for that location which is the furthest location from me AND it meant I needed to go back there which I didn't plan on doing. So I finally got my vegan bratwurst, ran late to pick up my boyfriend, and then got to try the Beyond sausage for the first time. 2 bites in, I couldn't stomach it and threw it away. So much for all that waiting and my free menu item coupons. I loved the Field Roast they used to have there and while I'm glad they've made a huge step in having an entire Plant Based vegan menu with Impossible Burgers and Sliders and 2 types of Beyond Sausage, it tastes too much like meat for me and it doesn't sit well in my stomach. I literally gave up meat because I didn't like the taste so it's great if you still like the taste, I just don't. I did go back to try it again when the circumstances weren't bad and I used those coupons (about a month later), and this time I did finish the hot dog, but it was more because I was hungry and it didn't make me sick that time even though I still didn't care for the taste. If you like the new vegan Beyond and Impossible, you'll probably like Dog Haus, but this location is now one I won't go to again.</Text><Pics>None<//Pics>< Resp>

<text>Located inside an old IHOP on the Western side of Reseda Blvd.  Very large parking lot located in the rear.  Small entry to the lot from Reseda that's easy to miss driving by. Much easier entry from Baird.  Menu consists of hot dogs, sausages, burgers, and sides.  Handful of beers on tap (pint, liter, or pitcher).  Burgers are well made and flavorful. Buns are King's Hawaiian Rolls (4-per burger), whichs sounds odd but works pretty well.  Utensils are located near the soft-drink machine you pass by on the way in.  Variety of tables and bar seating, with some available outdoors.  Service is decent.  Prices are on the high side, but not ridiculous and generally worth it.</text>< pics>

< Text>
I enjoyed the Holy Aioli Burger, which is one of my favorites. My husband enjoyed another fav, the Mench, which has plenty of pastrami on it. We also shared a side of well done tots. We called in the order and it was done within 5 minutes of my arrival. There's a nice bar top that I briefly waited at. If you live in the area, Dog Haus sends frequent coupons...BOGO burgers etc. Also, I received an additional 10% cash back through Yelp ü§ë My only complaint would be the fact that the Reseda street entrance is not accessible for entry/exiting, which is a safety issue given that there's only one other public exit.<//Text>
